6.  Appendix 2 shows key revisions in the original composition of the TA cluster. The 
revisions reflect the Government’s sectoral and capacity-building priorities with respect to ADB’s 
operations  and  program  in  India.  The  revisions  were  also  based  on  (i)  review  of  project 
readiness; (ii) revisions in the project processing schedule for 2006–2009; (iii) consultations with 
project executing agencies; (iv) reconsideration of the scope, suitability, and focus of the CTAs; 
and (v) suggestions of  the Department of Economic Affairs (DEA) and ADB sector managers.  

C.   Cost and Financing 

7.  The $15 million TAC is financed by the Government of the United Kingdom on a grant 
basis. The Government of India provides counterpart contributions in kind estimated at $4 
million. The revisions to the original list of CTAs included under the TA cluster have had no 
impact on the cost estimate and financing arrangements. The Government has agreed that 
approval of the CTAs does not commit ADB to finance any ensuing projects.
